Ukraine coach, Andriy Shevchenko, has backed England to reach the Euro 2020 final. Shevchenko said this following Ukraine’s Euro 2020 quarter-final 4-0 defeat England on Saturday night. England will play Denmark in the European championship semi-final on June 7. Euro 2020: Mourinho predicts quarter-final fixtures “I think that England played very pragmatically today,” Shevchenko said at his post-match press conference. “They used their strong flanks, they used our mistakes and they played very well, at a top-level. “But the English team is really strong – individually and as a team – and they have a great coach. They reached the semi-finals and I can see that this team can play in the final.”